<subSubSection id="00BB12ACFFC15772FF44E1D7FDB0CB38" pageId="6" pageNumber="5" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="481E4127FFC15772FF44E1D7FC82CD58" blockId="6.[192,1440,482,858]" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">
<emphasis id="7AD59D35FFC15772FF44E1D7FEEFCED8" bold="true" box="[192,349,482,506]" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">Discussion.</emphasis>
The leoni species group is composed of 7 species, 6 of which inhabit the Neotropical region (
<bibRefCitation id="2C303CD6FFC15772FF4CE237FDAACD38" author="Borkent, A. &amp; G. R. Spinelli" box="[200,536,514,538]" pageId="6" pageNumber="5" refId="ref13097" refString="Borkent, A., and G. R. Spinelli. 2007. Neotropical Ceratopogonidae (Diptera: Insecta). In: J. Adis, J. R. Arias, G. Rueda-Delgado, and K. M. Wantzen (eds). Aquatic biodiversity in Latin America (ABLA). Vol. 4. Pensoft; Sofia-Moscow. 198 p." type="book" year="2007">Borkent and Spinelli 2007</bibRefCitation>
). The 7 
<superScript id="BFD4EC6FFFC15772FDF2E234FD37CD2D" attach="left" box="[630,645,513,527]" fontSize="6" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">th</superScript>
species, 
<taxonomicName id="8FA13AA4FFC15772FD70E236FC0FCD38" authority="Wirth" authorityName="Wirth" authorityYear="1952" box="[756,957,514,538]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Culicoides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="reevesi">
<emphasis id="7AD59D35FFC15772FD70E236FCB5CD38" box="[756,775,515,538]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="7AD59D35FFC15772FC93E236FCDACD38" box="[791,872,515,538]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">reevesi</emphasis>
Wirth
</taxonomicName>
, is known in the Nearctic region from Arizona, California, New 
<collectingRegion id="8A658FC5FFC15772FE78E217FDE6CD18" box="[508,596,546,570]" country="Mexico" name="Mexico" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">Mexico</collectingRegion>
and Utah (
<bibRefCitation id="2C303CD6FFC15772FD64E217FC78CD18" author="Grogan, W. L., Jr. &amp; G. R. Spinelli &amp; R. A. Phillips &amp; D. L. Woodward" box="[736,970,546,570]" pageId="6" pageNumber="5" pagination="433 - 438" refId="ref13850" refString="Grogan, W. L., Jr., G. R. Spinelli, R. A. Phillips, and D. L. Woodward. 2004. The male of Culicoides reevesi Wirth, with a redescription of the female and new seasonal activity, distribution, and biting records (Diptera: Ceratopogonidae). Western North American Naturalist 64: 433 - 438." type="journal article" year="2004">Grogan et al. 2004</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="2C303CD6FFC15772FC52E217FAAFCD18" author="Borkent, A. &amp; W. L. Grogan, Jr." box="[982,1309,546,570]" pageId="6" pageNumber="5" pagination="1 - 48" refId="ref13013" refString="Borkent, A., and W. L. Grogan, Jr. 2009. Catalog of the New World biting midges north of Mexico (Diptera: Ceratopogonidae). Zootaxa 2273: 1 - 48." type="journal article" year="2009">Borkent and Grogan 2009</bibRefCitation>
). The only species previously known from this group in 
<collectingCountry id="30B601B7FFC15772FD5EE277FC83CD78" box="[730,817,578,602]" name="Mexico" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">Mexico</collectingCountry>
is 
<taxonomicName id="8FA13AA4FFC15772FCD5E276FB81CD78" authority="Ortiz" authorityName="Ortiz" authorityYear="1954" box="[849,1075,578,602]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Culicoides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gabaldoni">
<emphasis id="7AD59D35FFC15772FCD5E276FCD6CD78" box="[849,868,579,602]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="7AD59D35FFC15772FCEBE277FC5BCD78" box="[879,1001,578,602]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">gabaldoni</emphasis>
Ortiz
</taxonomicName>
, which is widely distributed in the Neotropical region (
<bibRefCitation id="2C303CD6FFC15772FE64E257FC96CD58" author="Borkent, A. &amp; G. R. Spinelli" box="[480,804,610,634]" pageId="6" pageNumber="5" refId="ref13097" refString="Borkent, A., and G. R. Spinelli. 2007. Neotropical Ceratopogonidae (Diptera: Insecta). In: J. Adis, J. R. Arias, G. Rueda-Delgado, and K. M. Wantzen (eds). Aquatic biodiversity in Latin America (ABLA). Vol. 4. Pensoft; Sofia-Moscow. 198 p." type="book" year="2007">Borkent and Spinelli 2007</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="481E4127FFC15772FF74E2B7FE62CC38" blockId="6.[192,1440,482,858]" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">
<taxonomicName id="8FA13AA4FFC15772FF74E2B7FE02CDB8" authorityName=": Wirth" authorityYear="1974" box="[240,432,642,666]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Culicoides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="leoni">
<emphasis id="7AD59D35FFC15772FF74E2B7FE02CDB8" box="[240,432,642,666]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">Culicoides leoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from other species in the leoni group by the following combination of characters: sensilla coeloconica on flagellomeres 1, 5-8; female wing length 0.63 mm; wing pattern with the caudal extension of the post-stigmatic pale spot not oblique in cell r3 and usually connected to vein M1; smaller pale spot on r-m crossvein; one pale spot in cell M1 near base; and distal pale spot in anal cell abutting wing margin.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="481E4127FFC15772FF74E317FC7DCC78" blockId="6.[192,1440,482,858]" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">
This species was previously known from 
<collectingCountry id="30B601B7FFC15772FD54E317FC84CC18" box="[720,822,802,826]" name="Ecuador" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="2C303CD6FFC15772FCC6E317FBCCCC18" author="Borkent, A. &amp; G. R. Spinelli" box="[834,1150,802,826]" pageId="6" pageNumber="5" refId="ref13097" refString="Borkent, A., and G. R. Spinelli. 2007. Neotropical Ceratopogonidae (Diptera: Insecta). In: J. Adis, J. R. Arias, G. Rueda-Delgado, and K. M. Wantzen (eds). Aquatic biodiversity in Latin America (ABLA). Vol. 4. Pensoft; Sofia-Moscow. 198 p." type="book" year="2007">Borkent and Spinelli 2007</bibRefCitation>
), and 
<collectingCountry id="30B601B7FFC15772FB45E317FA86CC18" box="[1217,1332,802,826]" name="Colombia" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">Colombia</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="2C303CD6FFC15772FAC6E317FEF1CC78" author="Spinelli, G. R. &amp; E. Santamaria &amp; O. L. Cabrera &amp; M. M. Ronderos &amp; M. F. Suarez" pageId="6" pageNumber="5" pagination="81 - 92" refId="ref15036" refString="Spinelli, G. R., E. Santamaria, O. L. Cabrera, M. M. Ronderos, and M. F. Suarez. 2009. Five new species of Culicoides Latreille described from Colombia, yielding a new species list and country records (Diptera: Ceratopogonidae). Memorias do Instituto Oswaldo Cruz 104: 81 - 92." type="journal article" year="2009">Spinelli et al. 2009</bibRefCitation>
). We provide the first records of 
<taxonomicName id="8FA13AA4FFC15772FD48E376FC9ACC78" authorityName=": Wirth" authorityYear="1974" box="[716,808,834,858]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Culicoides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="leoni">
<emphasis id="7AD59D35FFC15772FD48E376FD6DCC78" box="[716,735,835,858]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="7AD59D35FFC15772FD68E377FC9ACC78" box="[748,808,834,858]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">leoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry id="30B601B7FFC15772FCEBE377FC79CC78" box="[879,971,834,858]" name="Mexico" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">Mexico</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="481E4127FFC15772FF44E3B7FDF0CC98" blockId="6.[192,1440,898,1050]" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">
<emphasis id="7AD59D35FFC15772FF44E3B7FE4BCCB8" bold="true" box="[192,505,898,922]" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">
New records. 
<collectingRegion id="8A658FC5FFC15772FEFFE3B7FE4BCCB8" box="[379,505,898,922]" country="Mexico" name="Veracruz de Ignacio de la Llave" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">Veracruz</collectingRegion>
</emphasis>
, Huatusco, Rancho Tenejapa, 
<date id="3C1F67E7FFC15772FCECE3B6FC46CCB8" box="[872,1012,898,923]" pageId="6" pageNumber="5" value="1993-05-07">7 May 1993</date>
, H. Huerta, colecta con aspirador, 
<specimenCount id="5EA78AAEFFC15772FA15E3B7FE92CC98" pageId="6" pageNumber="5" type="female">2 females</specimenCount>
. 
<emphasis id="7AD59D35FFC15772FEAEE397FDF0CC98" bold="true" box="[298,578,930,954]" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">New country record.</emphasis>
</paragraph>
